.TH LPF-PLAN 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.0-dev" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-plan \- compile policy to a typed backend change plan
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf plan <policy>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compile policy into a typed backend change plan.
Plans include nftables, routing, tc, conntrack, logging, sysctl, and rollback preimage requirements.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-json
emit machine\-readable plan output
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf plan /etc/lpf.conf
lpf plan \-\-json /etc/lpf.conf
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Planning is read\-only but may inspect current host capabilities.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-diff(8), lpf\-apply(8)
